article.description: Aaryn Ellenberg scored a career-high 26 points, leading Oklahoma to a 116-66 victory over Texas-Pan American in the Basketball Travelers Invitational round-robin tournament.
article.headline: Aaryn Ellenberg scores career-high 26 points in Oklahoma rout
article.linkText: Sooners never trail in big win vs. Texas Pan-Am
article.story:
NORMAN, Okla. -- Aaryn Ellenberg scored a career-high 26 points, leading Oklahoma (No. 10 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) to a 116-66 victory over Texas-Pan American on Friday night in the Basketball Travelers Invitational round-robin tournament.

Ellenberg, a freshman, was 9-of-15 from the field, including 4-of-6 from behind the 3-point line for Oklahoma (4-0). The Sooners never trailed and led 56-30 at halftime.

OU will play Gardner-Webb in the second game of the tournament at 2 p.m. Saturday.

Senior Danielle Robinson, a preseason All-American, moved into seventh on the all-time scoring list at Oklahoma and finished with 16 points, missing only 3-of-11 shots.

The Sooners shot 56 percent -- they came in shooting 48.7 percent -- and scored a season high for points. Joanna McFarland had 13 points and 15 rebounds for the Sooners.

Texas' Bianca Torre scored a team-high 26 points. The Broncos (4-1) will take on Prairie View A&M at 7 p.m. Saturday.
